-- Spain's BFA pays back 9.9 bln eur in state-backed bond issues
-- By Sarah White
-- Fri Aug 22, 2014 08:44AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, Aug 22 (Reuters) - Spain's Banco Financiero y de Ahorros (BFA), the government-owned holding company which controls Bankia <BKIA.MC>, said on Friday it had redeemed early 9.9 billion euros (13.14 billion US dollars) in two state-guaranteed bond issues.

